President Biden and UN Secretary-General Guterres met to discuss the strong partnership between the United States and the United Nations. They emphasized the importance of multilateralism and the defense of democracy and international law. They also discussed the urgent need to address the COVID-19 pandemic, prepare for future health security threats, combat climate change, strengthen food systems and security, address humanitarian needs, prevent conflict, and promote human rights globally. President Biden highlighted the United Nations' unique role in delivering prosperity, peace, and security for all.